40|$|Public {{health is}} {{recognized}} by the <b>new</b> <b>social,</b> environmental and economic standards as a valuable resource that must be preserved and improved. The promotion of health needs {{a new system of}} health building that can answer to the <b>new</b> <b>social</b> <b>demand.</b> In this scenario, the “Health City” constitutes a complex building with integrated functions and services (health support, research, development, hospitality, technology and business incubator) that enhances the quality of health services. The “Health City” is a “new function” in which the treatment of diseases is the generative element of the system but non necessarily the primary function. This paper presents a meta-project that has been created with the aim to identify the correct balance between the different functions {{in order to create a}} synergetic interaction between the activities that form the “Health City”...|$|R
40|$|In {{the last}} ten years the global meat {{industry}} has encountered numerous critical events related to food safety and food quality. These events in turn have caused the industry to re-evaluate how the meat supply chain functions and how to service the <b>new</b> <b>social</b> attributes <b>demanded</b> in the market place. This paper uses a unique methodology, shedding light on why and how the US meat industry is evolving and why its evolutionary path may differ from that which is occurring in Europe. 1. Background In {{the last ten}} years the global meat industry has encountered numerous critical events related to food safety and food quality. These events in turn have caused the industry to reevaluate how the meat supply chain functions and how to service the <b>new</b> <b>social</b> attributes <b>demanded</b> in the market place. Issues like source-verified, non-GMO, and organic are becoming important sources of product differentiation. How should firms in the meat supply chain respond...|$|R
